1 4. Upon receipt of a request from the Board submitted
2 pursuant to subsection 3, if the Department determines that the
3 prisoner:
4 (a) Meets the criteria set forth in subsection 1, the Department
5 shall:
6 (1) Notify the Board of the prisoner’s eligibility for
7 consideration of second look parole;
8 (2) Place the prisoner on the next available list of persons
9 eligible for parole pursuant to NRS 209.254; and
10 (3) Provide to the Board a report prepared in accordance
11 with paragraph (c) of subsection 1 of NRS 213.131.
12 (b) Does not meet the criteria set forth in subsection 1, the
13 Department shall notify the Board and explain the reasons for
14 such a determination.
15 5. Upon receipt of the list prepared pursuant to NRS 209.254,
16 the Board shall, after sending copies of the list to all law
17 enforcement agencies in this State and other appropriate persons
18 in accordance with subsection 5 of NRS 213.1085, schedule a
19 hearing to consider the second look parole of an eligible prisoner
20 whose name appears on the list.
21 6. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 7, the Board
22 shall schedule and conduct the second look parole hearing of a
23 prisoner in the same general manner in which other prisoners are
24 considered for parole. The Board shall notify the prisoner and, if
25 applicable, the person who submitted the application pursuant to
26 subsection 2 of the date, time and location of the second look
27 parole hearing.
28 7. In determining whether to grant second look parole to a
29 prisoner, the Board shall consider:
30 (a) The written application and supporting documentation
31 submitted to the Board pursuant to subsection 2;
32 (b) The age of the prisoner at the time the offense was
33 committed in conjunction with any relevant research presented at
34 the hearing concerning the developmental maturity of persons at
35 that age;
36 (c) The age of the prisoner at the time the application was
37 submitted pursuant to subsection 2 in conjunction with any
38 relevant research presented at the hearing concerning the impact
39 of aging on the behavior of a person;
40 (d) Whether the prisoner had less involvement in the
41 commission of the crime for which parole is being considered than
42 other persons who participated in the commission of the crime;
43 (e) The behavior of the prisoner while in custody, including,
44 without limitation:
45 (1) Any disciplinary action taken against the prisoner; and
