1 provision of law, a prisoner who was sentenced [as an adult] for an
2 offense that was committed when he or she was less than [18] 25
3 years of age is eligible for parole as follows:
4 (a) For a prisoner who is serving a period of incarceration for
5 having been convicted of an offense or offenses that did not result in
6 the death of a victim, after the prisoner has served 15 calendar years
7 of incarceration, including any time served in a county jail.
8 (b) For a prisoner who is serving a period of incarceration for
9 having been convicted of an offense or offenses that resulted in the
10 death of only one victim, after the prisoner has served 20 calendar
11 years of incarceration, including any time served in a county jail.
12 2. The provisions of this section do not apply to a prisoner who
13 is serving a period of incarceration for having been convicted of an
14 offense or offenses that resulted in the death of two or more victims.
15 Sec. 4. The amendatory provisions of sections 1 and 3 of this
16 act apply to an offense committed before, on or after January 1,
17 2026.
18 Sec. 5. 1. This section becomes effective upon passage and
19 approval.
20 2. Sections 1 to 4, inclusive, of this act become effective:
